// Fixture: R2b documented-gap probe — symbolic-target selector ctor stays
// silent on the value-eval path (the 'before' state proving the positive
// deliverable is unbuilt).
//
// PRD: docs/prds/v0_6/value-eval-geometry-addressing.md (Leaf R2b)
//
// A symbolic-target selector constructor `faces_by_normal(box(...), vec3(...))`
// with INLINE args over a freshly-constructed (unrealized) box handle. The
// selector dispatcher resolves its target/dir args via values.get(cell_id);
// inline `box(...)` / `vec3(...)` FunctionCall args have no bound cell id, so
// they fall through to None and the selector ctor cannot run on the value-eval
// path. Value::Selector is constructed ONLY on the build path
// (build_leaf_selector, reached solely via try_eval_topology_selector ←
// post_process_topology_selectors in engine_build.rs); there is NO box arm and
// NO faces_by_normal arm in any reify-stdlib eval_* module. So `f` falls
// through to Value::Undef and the cell resolves to `undef`.
//
// Live ground-truth (debug binary): `reify eval` →
//     FacesByNormalSymbolicEvalSilent.f = undef
//   EVAL_EXIT=0, no `EvalError` on stderr.
//
// Because nothing surfaces a typed-consumer resolution failure here, eval must
// emit NOTHING (no E_EVAL_UNRESOLVED, no error-severity diagnostic). Reuse of
// 4118 build_leaf_selector on the eval path (making faces_by_normal(box())
// yield a Selector when consumed) is the UNBUILT deliverable.
//
// ir-probe observation model (PRD §4 / §6 G6(b)): exit 0 (clean) → ABSENT
// regardless of the asserted signature → PASS. Twin of uncons_box_no_error.ri.

structure def FacesByNormalSymbolicEvalSilent {
    let f = faces_by_normal(box(50mm, 30mm, 10mm), vec3(0mm, 0mm, 1mm))
}
